Heat a wide #frying pan{} over a high heat and add a splash of @oil{a splash}. When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{500%g} to the pan. Break it up with a #wooden spoon{}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and cook for ~{7%minutes} or until nicely browned. Get on with the rest of your prep as it cooks away.

Cut the @red onion{2} in half through the root. Peel and then chop into ½cm cubes or as small as you can. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Remove the core from the @red pepper{2} and slice as thinly as you can.

Once the beef has browned, add the red onion, red pepper and the @ras-el-hanout{2%tsp} and cook for another ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and then cook for ~{1%minute} before pouring in the @chopped tomatoes{2%400g cans}. Half fill the empty tin with water and add this to the pan. Stir in the @beef stock pot{2} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, reduce to medium-low heat and leave to bubble away for ~{20%minutes}.

While the beef cooks away, pop the @couscous{300%g} in a #bowl{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Mix in a glug of @olive oil{glug} and then pour in the @boiling water{600%ml}. Cover the bowl with #clingfilm{} or a #plate{} and leave for ~{10%minutes}.

Chop the top and bottom off the @courgette{2} and then cut into eight 1cm thick angled slices (see pic). Roughly chop the @coriander{10%stalks}.

Heat another frying pan over medium heat and toast the @flaked almonds{50%g} for ~{3%minutes} or until golden brown.

> Watch the almonds like a hawk, they burn very easily!

Once the almonds are out of the pan, increase the heat to high and and cook the courgettes for ~{5%minutes} on each side. Once nicely charred, remove your courgettes from the pan and keep until later.

Check the seasoning of the ragout and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Stir in your coriander and get ready to serve.

Spoon a bed of couscous into a bowl and then pop a couple of charred courgettes on top. Finish with your spiced beef ragout and a sprinkle of toasted almonds. Enjoy!